      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Think of the escrow account as a temporary safekeeper for the funds, holding onto the money until the closing date. On the closing day, the escrow agent releases the funds to you, and you transfer the ownership of the property to the seller. The actual transfer happens when the escrow agent disburses the funds, which is usually done electronically through a secure payment system. This process is facilitated by the escrow agent, ensuring a smooth transfer of funds and ownership.",
